com.blockhaus2000.minecraft.util.command

Interface CommandManager

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.bukkit.command.CommandExecutor
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleCommandManager

    public interface CommandManager
extends org.bukkit.command.CommandExecutor
    This command manager is used to execute the commands tagged with the Command annotation. This is a CommandExecutor.
    Author:
    Blockhaus2000
    See Also:
    CommandExecutor

    • Method Detail

      • register

        java.util.Set<CommandInfo> register(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                                  java.lang.Object obj)
        Registers all of the methods in the given Class that are tagged with the Command annotation.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class that holds of the tagged methods.
        obj - An Object of the given Class. Can be null if all of the methods are static.
        Returns:
        An Set of CommandInfos that are registered.

      • register

        java.util.Set<CommandInfo> register(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        Registers all of the methods in the given Class that are tagged with the Command annotation. Will call register(Class, Object) with obj = null.

        NOTE: Only call this if all of the tagged methods are static.

        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class that holds of the tagged methods.
        Returns:
        An Set of CommandInfos that are registered.
        See Also:
        register(java.lang.Class, java.lang.Object)

      • register

        java.util.Set<CommandInfo> register(java.lang.Object obj)
        Registers all of the methods in the given Class that are tagged with the Command annotation. Will call register(Class, Object) with clazz = Object.getClass().
        Parameters:
        obj - An Object of the given Class. Will be used to get the Class of the Object.
        Returns:
        An Set of CommandInfos that are registered.
        See Also:
        register(java.lang.Class, java.lang.Object)
